### Creator's Platform API Testing
### Save this file as test.rest or test.http and use REST Client extension in VS Code

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000
@userId = 

### 1. Check if server is running
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### 2. Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Creator",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Register another user
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane@example.com",
  "password": "securepass456"
}

### 4. Try to register with duplicate email (ERROR CASE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate User",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "anotherpass"
}

### 5. Try to register without password (ERROR CASE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Incomplete User",
  "email": "incomplete@example.com"
}

### 6. Get all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users

### 7. Get user by ID (Replace ID in URL)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/INSERT_USER_ID_HERE

### 8. Get user with invalid ID (ERROR CASE)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/invalidid

### 9. Update user
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/INSERT_USER_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name"
}

### 10. Update user email
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/INSERT_USER_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newemail@example.com"
}

### 11. Try to update with duplicate email (ERROR CASE)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/users/INSERT_USER_ID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "jane@example.com"
}

### 12. Delete user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/INSERT_USER_ID_HERE

### 13. Try to get deleted user (ERROR CASE)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/users/ID_OF_DELETED_USER

### 14. Try to delete non-existent user (ERROR CASE)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/users/000000000000000000000000
